Introduction
A traffic sign recognition program using Convolutional (CNN) and Computer Vision to detect traffic sign images and be able to label what they are.
Goal/Purpose:
This project is created for the fulfillment of requirements for the final project of 6INTELSYS. The topic chosen was the creation of a traffic sign recognition program with CNN and utilizing Reinforcement Learning for machine learning. This kind of program is usually used in the creation of autonomous vehicles or self-driving vehicles that require the use of real time video recognition of traffic signs to safely drive. It can also be used to determine the different kinds of traffic signs which may help new drivers in learning the different signs seen on the road. This notebook contains the necessary information about the project, what to install, and how to run the necessary programs using the dataset provided.
 
Questions to be Answered:
How accurate will the program be when using CNN?
Will Reinforcement Learning be effective for the training of model?
Will the traffic sign recognition program be accurate to be utilized in future projects?
 
Assumptions/Methodology/Scope:
Briefly describe assumptions, processing steps, and the scope of this project.
This project will be using a labeled dataset and will train a CNN model using reinforced learning. Our assumptions are that this model will work as intended and will be able to determine the traffic sign by labeling their names as their pictures are shown. A dataset folder with categorized images will be processed and used for training and validation and this dataset will only be limited to Philippine traffic signs and all signs available in the dataset.
 
Data Description
Content:
This dataset is a zip file of 14 data points which contains 2024 images. These images are categorized by the traffic sign.
Acknowledgements:
This dataset is provided by Jerry (Philippine Traffic Sign Dataset Computer Vision Model) and the original source can be found on https://universe.roboflow.com/jerry-imbhm/philippine-traffic-sign-dataset-9kz1e-qvpnr.
